installing dakota on the ubuntu 14.04
1. step 1:
downloaded dakota: 
Dakota 6.4 
https://dakota.sandia.gov/download.html
in bashrc 
alias dakota640='/home/gadar/Documents/softwares_new/dakota-6.4.0/bin/dakota'
export INSTALL_DIR=/home/gadar/Documents/softwares_new/dakota-6.4.0
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:$INSTALL_DIR/lib:$INSTALL_DIR/bin



libmpi_cxx.so.1 not found error. 
2. step 2: sudo apt install libblacs-mpi-dev

3. Re: How-To: Solving libXM.so.4 error shold install libmotif4:

sudo apt-get install libmotif4
